Bioinformatics Assignment 01

Ty Tran

Step 1: Download Split_contigs.zip to the computer
Step 2: Unzip Split_contigs.zip
Step 3: Get into: Finder -> Application -> Utilities (bottom) -> Terminal
Step 4: Combine all 360 contigs of Split_contigs.zip into one file

Step 5: Make sure direction is at Genome (directory includes Split_contigs)
Navigate
$ pwd
$ cd /Users/Genome/Split_contigs 

Step 6: Using "cat": 
$ cat contig* > CombinedContigs

Step 7: Counting by "grep"
Count number of As
$ grep -v "^>" CombinedContigs | grep -o A | wc -l 
Result: 1075568

Count number of Ts
$ grep -v "^>" CombinedContigs | grep -o T | wc -l 
Result: 1083540

Count number of Gs
$ grep -v "^>" CombinedContigs | grep -o G | wc -l 
Result: 2164972

Count number of Cs
$ grep -v "^>" CombinedContigs | grep -o C | wc -l 
Result: 2158760

Step 8: Applying "echo" 
$ number1=1075568
$ number2=1083540
$ number3=2164972
$ number4=2158760

Echo to calculate total nucleotides
$ echo $((number1+number2+number3+number4))
Result: 6482840

Echo to calculate total GCs
$ echo $((number3+number4))
Result: 4323732

$ number34=4323732
$ number1234=6482840

Echo to calculate the % GC content
$ echo $((number34*100/number1234))
Result: 66

